  <section id="problem">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header fade-up">
        <span class="section-number" style="color:#444;">02 — Problem</span>
        <span class="tag tag--rust">Problem Definition</span>
        <h2>What Is Broken<br>About This Space?</h2>
        <p>
          Montefiore Square has long suffered from a set of interconnected design and 
          programmatic failures. Understanding these is the foundation for meaningful redesign.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-grid stagger-children">
        <div class="problem-card">
          <span class="prob-num">01</span>
          <h3>Underactivation</h3>
          <p>
            The plaza lacks seating, shade, and programming. It functions primarily as a 
            pass-through space rather than a destination. There is no reason for residents to 
            linger, gather, or return. The absence of vendors and activities leaves the space 
            feeling vacant even during peak pedestrian hours.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="problem-card">
          <span class="prob-num">02</span>
          <h3>Hostile Hardscape</h3>
          <p>
            The plaza is dominated by exposed concrete and asphalt surfaces that absorb heat, 
            create uncomfortable glare, and provide zero ecological value. There is minimal 
            tree canopy, no planted areas, and no sensory variation — making the space harsh 
            in summer and bleak in winter.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="problem-card">
          <span class="prob-num">03</span>
          <h3>No Market Infrastructure</h3>
          <p>
            Despite strong informal vending culture in the surrounding neighborhood, the plaza 
            has no dedicated vendor kiosks, power access, or market layout. Local entrepreneurs 
            have no formal, weather-protected space to operate — limiting both economic activity 
            and cultural expression in the public realm.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

