        <span class="tag tag--rust" style="margin-bottom:16px;">Conclusion</span>
        <p style="font-size:1.05rem;line-height:1.85;color:#ccc;max-width:800px;">
          Montefiore Square has the physical potential and community context to become one 
          of Harlem's most active and beloved small plazas. This proposal does not attempt 
          to impose a generic "design" solution — it attempts to listen to the site, 
          amplify existing community patterns, and create infrastructure that local people 
          can genuinely own. AI was a useful partner in the visualization process, but the 
          design decisions belonged to the human designer who understood what the community 
          actually needs.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

